    "body": "SGLang's AWQ quantization path on AMD GPUs goes through Triton-based\ndequantization (awq_dequantize_triton in awq_triton.py) rather than the\nMarlin kernels used on NVIDIA. This path has been functional but had no CI\ncoverage, meaning regressions could ship undetected. This PR registers\ntest_awq.py for the AMD CI suite so the Mixtral-8x7B AWQ-INT4 MoE eval\nruns on MI300X/MI325X hardware.\n\nThe existing test file contains three test classes: TestAWQ (which exercises\nthe Triton dequant path used on HIP), and two AWQ Marlin variants that\nexplicitly pass --quantization awq_marlin. Since is_awq_marlin_compatible\nreturns False on HIP and the Marlin GEMM kernels are CUDA-only, the Marlin\nclasses are skipped in AMD CI via @unittest.skipIf(is_in_amd_ci(), ...).\n\nSeparately, there was no documentation anywhere that told AMD users which\nquantization methods actually work on their hardware. I audited every method\nregistered in QUANTIZATION_METHODS (and the conditional mxfp4 entry), traced\nthe backend dispatch in each config class to determine HIP compatibility, and\nadded a platform compatibility table to quantization.md. The table covers all\n18+ methods with their NVIDIA/AMD support status and notes on which backend\n(Aiter, Triton, vLLM, etc.) is used on each platform.\n\nThe AMD GPU doc (amd_gpu.md) also had no mention of quantization at all, so\nI added a section with practical notes on what works, the SGLANG_USE_AITER=1\nsetup, runnable examples, and the list of unsupported methods (awq_marlin,\ngptq_marlin, gguf, modelopt_fp8, modelopt_fp4, petit_nvfp4).\n\n## Test plan\n\n- AWQ Triton path CI: test_awq.py::TestAWQ registered for\n  stage-b-test-large-1-gpu-amd (est. 200s). Runs MMLU eval (64 examples)\n  on hugging-quants/Mixtral-8x7B-Instruct-v0.1-AWQ-INT4, threshold > 0.64.\n- Marlin classes (TestAWQMarlinBfloat16, TestAWQMarlinFloat16) confirmed\n  skipped on AMD CI via is_in_amd_ci() guard.\n- Doc links verified: quantization.md#platform-compatibility anchor exists,\n  cross-reference from amd_gpu.md resolves correctly.",
    "created_at": "2026-02-28T07:08:20Z",
